This paper deals with geometric arrangements of rectangles in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses combinatorial arrangements and intersection graphs, which are common themes in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The study of arrangements and graphs often involves algorithms and data structures, which fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper touches upon the squarability problem, which is related to geometric rigidity and graph drawing, both of which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT).
